  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Mary Gray Chapman returns Deborah Weston&apos;s ruff. She is thankful that Deborah&apos;s letters have arrived with &quot;as favourable intelligence of Henry&apos;s health as we could resonably hope.&quot; [Henry is probably a reference to Henry Grafton Chapman.] Mother has been very ill and now recovering, and regains her health slowly.</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">On a separate leaf, there is an extract of a letter by Mme. Dupuy; it was transcribed by Mary Gray Chapman and sent to Deborah Weston. Mrs. Dupuy writes that Mr. &amp; Mrs. Chapman have sailed for Port au Prince. She describes their travel plans and expresses the pleasure derived from their visit.</subfield>
